<span class="line"><span style="color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#B392F0">openclaw</span><span style="color:#2B5581;--shiki-dark:#9DB1C5"> models</span><span style="color:#2B5581;--shiki-dark:#9DB1C5"> status</span></span>
<span class="line"><span style="color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#B392F0">openclaw</span><span style="color:#2B5581;--shiki-dark:#9DB1C5"> doctor</span></span>
</code></pre></div></div><div class="print:hidden" data-fade-overlay="true" aria-hidden="true" style="--fade-color-light:#ffffff;--fade-color-dark:#1f1f1f"></div></div>
<span data-as="p">What they do:</span>
<ul>
<li><code>openclaw status</code>: quick snapshot of gateway/agent health + basic config.</li>
<li><code>openclaw models status</code>: checks provider auth + model availability.</li>
<li><code>openclaw doctor</code>: validates and repairs common config/state issues.</li>
</ul>
<span data-as="p">Other useful CLI checks: <code>openclaw status --all</code>, <code>openclaw logs --follow</code>,
<code>openclaw gateway status</code>, <code>openclaw health --verbose</code>.</span>
<span data-as="p">Quick debug loop: <a href="faq#first-60-seconds-if-somethings-broken" class="link">First 60 seconds if something’s broken</a>.
Install docs: <a class="link" href="https://docs.openclaw.ai/install">Install</a>, <a class="link" href="../install/installer">Installer flags</a>, <a class="link" href="../install/updating">Updating</a>.</span>
